wikipedia_page.main: Frederick James Hyland (16 December 1893 — 27 February 1964) was an English cricketer who played for Hampshire. He was born in Battle and died in Hartford, Cheshire.Hyland made a single first-class appearance, during the 1924 County Championship season, against Northamptonshire. However, the match was abandoned after two overs with just a single run on the board. Hyland fielded, but did not bat or bowl.
